                        <msItem n="2" xml:id="a2">
                            <locus from="17b" to="18a">ff. 17b-18a</locus>
                            <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                            <note type="content-genre">Astronomy</note>
                            <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">[Ikhtīyārāt-i ayyām]</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ara">[اختیارات ایام]</title>                            
                            <author>
                                    <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Unknown.</persName>
                                    <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="org"/>
                                    <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="alt"/>
                                    <persName xml:lang="ara"/>
                            </author>
                            <note>Ikhtīyārāt-i ayyām is a general title for treatises outlining auspiciousness and inauspiciousness of days, weeks, New Year Day, months, 
                                hours and other essentials, extracted from relaiable sources. The most importnt sources available under the title of Ikhtīyārāt belong to
                                ʿAllāmah Majlisī and Mullā Ḥusayn Kashifī. The authors of this copy and the manuscript No. 377 (FAW 18) are, however, both unknown, and the
                                copies are also different to the works of Majlisī and Kashifī.     
                            </note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="per">مطلب اول در اختیارات. اول بگرمابه شدن باید که قمر بیکی از خانهای مریخ و مشتری بود… 
                            </incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="per">… باید قمر اندر هبوط و زحل ساقط و … و ضعیف و منحوس باشد والله العالم بحقایق الامور.
                            </explicit>
